# Python (Blender scripts)
__pycache__/

# Belt-and-braces: Godot's glTF importer default (embedded_image_handling=1,
# Extract Textures) writes loose copies of the baked textures next to the
# .glb files even though the .glb embeds them. The .glb.import files now pin
# mode 3 (Embed as Uncompressed) so extraction should not happen; if it ever
# does again (e.g. a fresh import regenerating defaults), keep the strays out
# of the repo - deleting them out from under Godot's import cache corrupts
# it (null PackedScene loads) until .godot/imported is wiped and reimported.
# DEF-07 confirmed the "if it ever does again" case is real: six brand new
# .glb files imported with Godot's default mode 1 and extracted their textures,
# and the rules below covered only two of the three names bake.py actually
# writes (_diff, _norm, _orm - _rough is packed into the ORM and removed), so
# _norm and _orm turned up untracked. Pinning mode 3 in the new .glb.import
# files stopped it; these patterns are the belt-and-braces, now complete.
game/assets/models/*_diff.png
game/assets/models/*_rough.png
game/assets/models/*_norm.png
game/assets/models/*_orm.png
game/assets/models/*_diff.png.import
game/assets/models/*_rough.png.import
game/assets/models/*_norm.png.import
game/assets/models/*_orm.png.import
